args:
The party safely retrieves Simurgh's egg from
the fiends. While the prince misses his chance
to win the egg hunt, he is hailed as a hero for
his part in saving the forest. His wish for
friendship between humans and sylvans is
fulfilled, albeit not how he originally planned.
Intent on retrieving Simurgh's egg, the party\nscours the forest for the fiends' nest.
There's the nest—which means that\ngiant egg must be Simurgh's.
I've never seen so many fiends before...
Probably best not to go charging in.\nSylas, Luca—got any goodies you\nwanna share?
I used the last of my aroma oil earlier.\nWhat about your smoke bombs, Luca?
I've only got a mustardbomb left,\nand that'll just rile them up.
Hmm. I think I have an idea.\nSo...
It sounds like it'll work—but won't you be\nin a ton of danger?
Yeah... If one person fumbles their part,\nyou could end up in major trouble.
Plus, you barely even know me and Sylas.
You sure you can trust us?
I am. I've seen how skilled you both are.
Plus, you're Luca's friends, so you should\nbe used to dealing with reckless behavior.
H-hey now, what's that supposed to mean?
Nya ha ha! That's your reason for\ntrusting us with your life?\nYou're a riot, {player_name}!
Well all right; count me in.
I have no objections. There is some\nrisk, but the strategy you outlined\nis indeed the most pragmatic.
Don't worry, nobody's gonna leave\nyou hangin'!
Oh, I know.\nAll right everyone, get in position!
That got their attention. Just have to\nlead them to the right spot now...
Hey fiends—over here!\nCome and get me!
There he is! Heh, he really pulled it off.
Keep your eyes peeled for the signal.
Aye aye, cap'n! All right fiends,\nhere's some arrows comin' at ya!
...Or rather, those mushrooms at your feet!
Bold move, luring those fiends right into\na spore trap.
Yeah, and GENIUS! It took 'em all out\nat once! Now, Simurgh—blow those\nspores away!
*gasp* Phew, I managed to hold\nmy breath.
I'm fine. I think I just *cough* inhaled a\nfew spores.
We'll handle this from here.\nYou just rest, yeah?
...Whew, I think that's all of 'em.\nHow's the prince?
Sylas whipped up an antidote,\nso he should be fine.

We've only just met, yet you devised
a strategy that relied on me to save
your very life. I should judge you
foolish, but...I shall settle for brave.
Heh. Thanks, Sylas. \nHave you seen Sarisse and Fleur?
They should be back any minute now\nwith ol' Simurgh's egg.
We did it! We got the egg!
Oh, my darling...\nNever leave me again.

I'm glad we could help, Simurgh. You may
have a more peaceful time raising your
egg elsewhere, though; you'd be more
than welcome at my castle.
Hey, yeah! No fiends to worry about there.
My, what a kind offer.\nI will gladly accept.
Excuse the interruption, but we're fast\napproaching the end of the egg hunt.
Shoot—if we're not back to the village\nin time, we'll be disqualified!
We'll never make it...\nWhat a dumb rule!
Please, allow me to ferry you back.\nIt's the least I can do.
Damn, if we zip through the sky we'll\nbe back in no time!
I'm afraid I can only manage\none passenger, however.
So... Only one of us can have their\nwish granted?
...I shall withdraw myself from selection.\nMy entry was never under my own behest.
As such, I plan to seek knowledge from\nbeyond the forest.
To that end, I would very much welcome\nyour help, Luca. You seem quite\nwell-versed in the outside world.
HELL yeah, man! Whatever you need.
Dang it Sylas, you beat me to the punch!
Are you planning on giving up the hunt\nas well?
Yeah, I guess. But that doesn't\nmean I'm giving up on Sarisse and\nLuca—not even close! Nya ha ha!
Anyway, I can still count on you for\nadvice, right? I figure I'll need it,\nsooner or later.
Are you sure?\nLike you said, I'm not sylvan.
Eh, whatever. You trusted all us sylvans\nwith your life, right? I figure I can do\nthe same.
Well, that's Laranoa and I spoken for.\nWho shall Simurgh carry, then?
Good question. \nI think it should be...
Everyone, your attention please!\nThe hour has arrived to crown the\nwinner of the egg hunt!
She made quite an entrance,\nreturning atop a dragon.
I present to you, your champion...\nFLEUR!
Ha ha! Thank you so much!
Now, let us close out the Banquet in style.\nEat, drink, and be merry all!
*pant* *pant* Man, I gotta work on my\ncardio. Looks like we can still catch\nthe end, though.
I need to get me some GRUB!
The young girl won... Are you all truly\nall right with ceding the victory to her?
Course! It seemed the best way to go,\nall things considered.
Yeah. I only wanted to win so the elders\nwould accept more cultural exchange.
But it actually wouldn't have done much\ngood, right {player_name}?
Yeah. That's something we came to\nrealize, working with Laranoa and Sylas.

We can't hope to improve sylvan and
human relations with a law alone.
We need to trust each other first,
and go from there.
So we'll work at it, bit by bit,\nand then someday our wish will\ncome true—without even making it.
Guys! Oh my gosh, thank you all SO much!

The elders gave me permission
to leave the village! Well, I guess
I kinda forced them, but STILL—
now I can study human art!
Congrats, girl! I can't wait to see\nwhat you come up with.
You'll be the first person I show!
Hey, is that the human prince\nI heard about?
Must be. The champion told me he\nrisked his life to beat some fiends!
Yeah, that's him! I'd be fertilizer\nif he hadn't saved me from that\nraging dragon.
Wait a minute... Didn't he also save the\nvillage at Myriage Lake from the Empire?\nSounds like a hero to me.
O-oh, uh... I'm just happy I could help.
Seems like we made some pretty good\nprogress today, eh prince?
Heh. You might be right, Luca.
Hey, everyone—let's lift this guy up\nand give him three cheers! Show him\nhow loud and proud we sylvans can be!
But first, a little personal thank-you—\nWelcome to KAPOW CITY!
Fawning over a human...\nAn utter disgrace!
And yet... To think a human would be met\nby such fervor...
Indeed; I doubt they would obey us,\neven if we bade them avoid humans.
Should the people wish to invite\nhim back in the future, we would\nnot be able to deny them.

...I suppose. To think our traditions
would be undone so easily...
Perhaps that too is a sign of
changing times.
This prince seems a very special character.\nOf that much, I am certain.
C'mon, Sarisse—let's get this guy\nin the air!
First cardio, now heavy lifting? Yeesh...\nYo, Sylas, get over here and help!
As the sun withdrew, the clear spring\nskies echoed with shouts of joy.
A fitting end for a lively and\nmemorable Vernal Banquet.
